        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Global Indian International School - Balewadi"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Vinay Padole"
          },
          "datePublished": "2025-02-27",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am extremely pleased with the experience my child has had at Global Indian International School, where he is currently in KG1, Division A. Over the past year, the school has created a wonderful and engaging learning environment, where my child has learned so much in a fun and playful way. The teachers are incredibly dedicated, making every lesson exciting and interactive.\n\nI also had the privilege of attending the school’s annual function, which was truly mesmerizing. Principal Munmun Chakraborty's speech about \"Our Littles Ones\" brought tears to my eyes, especially when she spoke about how parents and teachers work together in nurturing children. Her words about how parents take care of one child at home, while the school cares for so many, were so moving and true.\n\nA special mention to Kiran Ma'am, my child’s class teacher in Division A, for her unwavering dedication and tireless efforts throughout the year. She has not only helped my child prepare for the annual day performance, but also played a crucial role in his overall growth, learning, and understanding. Her personal care and attention have made a significant impact on his development.\n\nI would also like to extend my heartfelt appreciation to Priya Ma'am, the coordinator for the entire primary section. Her leadership and support have been invaluable in ensuring that everything runs smoothly and that every child is given the attention they need.\n\nThe school also does a wonderful job of celebrating all festivals, allowing the children to experience and learn about different cultures and traditions in a joyful and inclusive way. These celebrations add so much to their overall development and create lasting memories.\n\nAnother great feature is the regular weekly updates provided to parents, which include detailed PDFs of each day’s activities, along with poem links for revision at home. This makes it so easy to stay connected with what my child is learning and ensure we can reinforce that learning at home.\n\nAdditionally, the myGIIS mobile application has been incredibly helpful in keeping me informed. It's so easy to reach out to the class teacher for any queries, and I can get all the school notifications directly on the app. It also allows me to track my child’s progress, which gives me peace of mind and keeps me updated on his development.\n\nOverall, I am grateful for the positive experience and the wonderful impact the school has had on my child’s growth and development. Highly recommend!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
